<HEADLINE>
Large explosion hits Pakistan security post: official
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A large explosion followed by gunfire hit a Pakistani security
post late Tuesday in a restive northwestern district, an official
said, adding casualties were feared.
</P>
<P>
"There was a large explosion at a paramilitary checkpost in Swat
district, followed by gunfire," a security official told AFP,
adding they were trying to contact the security post for details
on casualties.
</P>
<P>
Swat valley, a hotbed of militant extremists, has seen numerous
clashes and bombings since radical pro-Taliban cleric Maulana
Fazlullah launched a violent campaign to enforce harsh Islamic
Sharia law in the region last year.
</P>
<P>
New Pakistan President Asif Ali Zardari has pledged to combat the
Islamic militancy that has been plaguing the country and
neighbouring Afghanistan.
</P>
